    "causal_summary": "`mk-goal.js` contains duplication and implicit contracts that made the F-series correctness bugs (fixed in phase 016) possible in the first place: the `sanitizeInlineText(x,160).replace(/\\s+/g,'-')` goal-ID normalization idiom is copy-pasted 7 times as of this phase starting (re-confirmed at mk-goal.js:1265, 1353, 1579, 1598, 1615, 1632, 1823 - grew from the originally-documented 6 sites after phases 016/017 added a 7th; re-verify via `rg` before implementing since this may have shifted further), plus a near-variant at `goalIdFromFactory` (mk-goal.js:487) using the same idiom internally",
